  <brief_title>PiCCO Guided Therapy in Liver Cirrhosis</brief_title>
  <official_title>Optimized Therapy of Decompensated Liver Cirrhosis by Hemodynamic Monitoring Using the PiCCO System</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Heidelberg University</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Heidelberg University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Prospective comparison of standard therapy in liver cirrhosis versus standard therapy plus
      intensified hemodynamic monitoring using the PiCCO system.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients presenting with advanced liver cirrhosis will receive either standard treatment or
      standard treatment plus hemodynamic monitoring with the PiCCO device. Fluids and vasoacitve
      drugs will be administered according to the measurements over a period of 5 days.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
